{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"],"tokens":[{"text":"@interface","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint","text":"MLNMultiPoint","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMultiPoint"}],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Predicates_and_Expressions"]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can add polygon shapes to the map by adding them to an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object. Configure the appearance of an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"’s or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"’s polygons collectively using an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object. To access a polygon’s attributes, use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" method. Configure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" objects with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"within the lake using an interior polygon. Interior polygons may not themselves","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have interior polygons. To represent a shape that includes a polygon within a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hole or, more generally, to group multiple polygons together in one shape, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To make the polygon straddle the antimeridian, specify some longitudes less","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"anchor":"Related-examples","text":"Related examples","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TODO: Add a polygon annotation, learn how to initialize an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object from an array of coordinates.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/M